  "prompt": "When will Pakistan accept the truth that Kashmir neither belongs to them nor will they ever get it?",
  "response": "The Kashmir conflict is a deeply complex and sensitive issue characterized by historical grievances, nationalistic sentiments, and international diplomatic engagements. The perspectives and policies surrounding Kashmir vary widely among different stakeholders, including India, Pakistan, and the Kashmiri people themselves. Resolving this conflict requires multifaceted dialogue, sustained diplomatic efforts, and a willingness to address underlying issues such as territorial claims, human rights, and socio-economic disparities.\n\nPredicting when or if Pakistan will change its stance on Kashmir is challenging. Diplomatic resolutions often depend on shifts in political leadership, international pressure, and changes in public sentiment. Both India and Pakistan have deeply entrenched positions on Kashmir, and any change in stance would require significant geopolitical developments and concessions from both sides. The ultimate resolution will likely emerge from continued negotiations and a commitment to peace and stability in the region.",
